(4, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'finance-and-operations', 'none', 'small-loans-for-small-business-stock-photo-19838792-sustainable-resources-1200.jpg', 'none', 'Small Loans for Small Businesses', 'none', 'LaToya M. Smith', 'none', 'Even before the credit crunch, traditional banks were skittish about approving microloans to newer firms and startups.', 'none', 'Even before the credit crunch, traditional banks were skittish about approving microloans to newer firms and startups. While businesses lending in amounts of more than $1 million turned upward, small business lending under $1 million remained restrained according to the Small Business Administration (http://www.sba.gov/advocacy/7540/173967). Access to capital and credit is paramount to the growth and success of small businesses and with banks postponing new borrowing and lending due to an uncertain economy, many firms have turned to microloans. Although the guidelines for lending are more flexible than traditional banks, each lender has its own lending and credit requirements. Heres how it works:<b>What can microloans be used for?</b>centers, start up and expand. or fixtures, machinery or equipment.<ul><li>The SBA provides loans up to $50,000 to help small businesses, and certain not-for-profit childcare</li><li>The loan, which is about $13,000 on average, can be used for working capital, inventory or supplies, furniture</li><li>You cannot use the monies to pay existing debts or to purchase real estate.</li></ul><b>Application Process:</b>The SBA backs lenders who provide loans to small businesses. If you apply for SBA microloan financing you may be required to participate in a business-training program designed to help you launch or expand your business before your loan can be considered. To get started youll need: personal guarantee of the business owner.<ul><li>Your social security number orindividual taxpayer identification number (ITIN)</li><li><span>Proof of income/cash flow</span></li><li><span>A business plan</span></li><li>Financial statements (tax returns,profit and loss statements, etc.)</li><li>**You may also need a personal andprofessional reference, and lenders typically require collateral or the</li></ul><b>Repayment terms, interest rates and fees:</b><span>Microloans are</span>generally between 8 and 13 percent and have a maximum repayment period of six years. The loan repayment terms will vary based on the loan amount, planned use of funds, requirements set by the intermediary lender and the needs of the small business owner.<b><i>Microlenders regularly report repayments to</i></b><b><i>the three credit lenders (Experian, Equifax and TransUnion.)</i></b><b>How to find a microloan provider:</b>your industry and state (<a title="" href="http://www.sba.gov/loans-and-grants"><span>http://www.sba.gov/loans-and-grants</span></a>).<span>&nbsp;</span><ul><li>Check out the SBA loan and grantssearch tool to help you find government-financing programs specific to</li></ul><span>ACCION,</span>a non-profit organization, provides low-to-moderate income business owners who cannot borrow from traditional banks due to business type, insufficient credit history or who have not been in business for a long time with access to capital and financial education. Loans range from $500 to $50,000 (<a title="" href="http://www.accionusa.org/"><span>http://www.accionusa.org/</span></a><span>).</span>', 'br', 1368734220, '', 'none', 'Small Loans for Small Businesses', 'none', 'How the SBA Microloan Program Works', 'none', 'Loans, Small Business, Microloan, SBA, Small Business Administration, Microloan Program', 'none', 'Small Loans for Small Business', 'none', 'stock-photo-8967215-loan-center.jpg', 'none', 'How the SBA Microloan Program Works', 'none', 'Journalist - Black Enterprise Magazine', 'none', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/latoyasmith', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '