(10, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'business-ink', 'none', '', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', '', 'none', 'Take it from me, I know from experience - words that sound like music to your ears when you want to avoid pit falls.', 'none', 'Take it from me, I know from experience words that could\n\nsound like music to your ears when you are trying to avoid a pit fall in your\nbusiness. An Entrepreneur.com article highlights these business lessons\nlearned from football, garlic and a shark.\n\n<b>Football</b>\n\nThe only way to learn, in football or in business, is by\nlosing. Former pro-football player Fran Tarkenton said about the failure he\nhas experienced in his business pursuits.\n\n<b>His business:</b>a food startup\n\n<b>His mistake:</b>a lack of personal research and letting someone else\nmake the decisions\n\n<b>The lesson:</b>(in his words) You cant rely on others to make you\nsuccessful\n\n<b>Garlic</b>\n\nI scream, you scream, we all scream for non-dairy, garlic\nflavored ice cream!!!\n\n*record scratches*\n\nNot so much huh?<span>&nbsp;</span>\nThats the response that Tofutti Mintz, famed maker of the non-dairy\nsweet treat received when he introduced his Krazy Garlic ice cream line.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>His business:</b>non-dairy ice cream\n\n<b>His mistake:</b>selecting an unappealing name for a product (and quite\nfrankly not thinking about the fact the garlic is probably not the best ICE\nCREAM flavor.\n\n<b>The lesson:</b>savory & sweet dont always mix, and what you name\nyour product (and your kids) is key to your marketing.<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>A Shark</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBarbara Corcoran, of ABCs<i>Shark Tank</i>, hasnt always been a real estate mogul. In fact, she\nwas some what of a florist before she got into real estate. Her current Shark\nstatus was once the equivalent of a minnow as she didnt go after her money\nwith that same tenacity, thereby losing her business.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b>Her business:</b>floral designer\n\n<b>Her mistake:</b>a lack of diversity in clientele and failure to hold\nher customers accountable\n\n<b>The</b><b>lesson:</b><span>make sure the success of your business is not</span>\nlargely dependant upon one customer, and dont be afraid to ask for what is due\nto you.\n\nYou can read the full article at Entrepreneur.com (http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/226651)<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n\n\n', 'br', 1369058580, '', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', '{filedir_1}shattered_@2X.png', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/226651', 'none', 'Lessons In Failure From Notable Entrepreneurs', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(11, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'business-ink', 'none', '', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', '', 'none', 'Social media, when used correctly, is a marketing tool that instantaneously alters the brand presence of your business.', 'none', 'Social media, when used correctly, is a marketing tool that instantaneously alters the brand presence of your business. Developing an impactful social media strategy transforms the growth and reach of your business. Similarly, the lack of an effective social\nmedia plan can create a disconnection with your intended audience.<span>&nbsp;</span>The social media manager works in concert\nwith the business owner to develop that successful plan.<span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>Below you will find questions to help business</span>\nowners identify the right social media manager for their companies.<span>The</span>\nfirst 10 questions are addressed to the business owner. Ask yourself these\nquestions to identify your business needs of this potential employee.<span>&nbsp;</span>The last 10 questions are questions to ask\nyour potential candidate. By concentrating on these questions, you will have\nthe right tools to increase your online presence.\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><b>Social Media Checklist</b><b>Questions to the business owner:</b><span>&nbsp;</span><span>1. What skill(s) are important to me? (i.e., writing,</span>\nstorytelling, marketing, customer service, sales, etc.)\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>2. What are my business goals?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>3. What are my business objectives?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>4. How will I define success? (ex. Contacts converted into sales</span>\nand inquiries? Posts generating good feedback, comments, page likes, page\nshares? Is traffic increasing to my site, services, and products every month on\na consistent basis?)\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>5. Will I pay a retainer, by the hour or by the project?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>6. What will my minimum contract period be? (month-to-month</span>\ntrial, quarterly, or six months, etc.)\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>7. What sites will I use to identify prospective candidates?</span><span></span>\n\n8. How are similar companies using social media?\n\n<span></span>\n\n9. How often will I check in with the social media manager to make sure my\ngoals and objectives are being met?\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>10. What type of content do I want my social media manager to</span>\ncreate? (Memes, video, Twitterchats, webinars, slideshows, livestreams).\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span></span><b>Interview Questions:</b><span>&nbsp;</span><span>1. What campaigns have you worked on? Please provide me with the</span>\ncontact information to some of your clients.\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>2. What ideas do you have for my business?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>3. Do you understand my industry and target market?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>4. Can you show me some of examples of your work? What were the</span>\nmeasureable results?\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>5. What tools do you use to measure ROI?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>6. What social media platforms do you think are best for my</span>\nbusiness?\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>7. What social media platforms do you specialize in?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>8. What are your payment terms?</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>9. How do you handle a social media crisis? Give me an example</span>\nof a challenge you faced and how you handled it.\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>10. What is your background, besides social media?</span>\n\n\n\n', 'br', 1369058760, '', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', '{filedir_1}shattered_@2X.png', 'none', 'Social Media Worksheet', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 