(12, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'marketing', 'none', '', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', '', 'none', 'Geoffrey James, Inc.Com writer of the Sales Source column, shared his 12 Great Motivational Quotes for 2013 for this year.', 'none', '<p>Geoffrey James, <a href="http://www.inc.com" target="_blank">Inc.com</a> writer of the Sales Source column, shared his <a href="http://www.inc.com/geoffrey-james/12-great-motivational-quotes-for-2013.html?nav=featured" target="_blank">12 Great Motivational Quotes for 2013</a> at the beginning of the year. As we settle into the second half we thought we would offer you some Mid-Year Motivation with 6 of those quotes below.</p>\n<ol><li>"A real decision is measured by the fact that you''ve taken a new action. If there''s no action, you haven''t truly decided." <i>Tony Robbins</i></li>\n<li>"You can have everything in life you want, if you will just help other people get what they want." <i>Zig Ziglar</i></li>\n<li>"The number of times I succeed is in direct proportion to the number of times I can fail and keep on trying." <i>Tom Hopkins</i></li>\n<li>"You have everything you need to build something far bigger than yourself." <i>Seth Godin</i></li>\n<li>"Cherish your visions and your dreams as they are the children of your soul, the blueprints of your ultimate achievements." <i>Napoleon Hill</i></li>\n<li>"If you can''t control your anger, you are as helpless as a city without walls waiting to be attacked." <i>The Book of Proverbs</i></li></ol>\n<p>You can read the full article on <a title="" href="http://www.inc.com/geoffrey-james/12-great-motivational-quotes-for-2013.html?nav=featured">Inc.com</a>.</p>\n', 'br', 1369059000, '', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', '{filedir_1}shattered_@2X.png', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'http://www.inc.com/geoffrey-james/12-great-motivational-quotes-for-2013.html?nav=featured', 'none', 'Quotes To Keep You Inspired On Your Business Journey', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Inc.com', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(13, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'business-ink', 'none', '', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '', 'none', 'Mike Jones, former MySpace CEO now CEO of Science, Inc, recently shared some advice on Entrepreneur Magazines Young Entrepre', 'none', 'Mike Jones, former MySpace CEO now CEO of Science, Inc, recently shared some advice on Entrepreneur Magazines Young Entrepreneur website on how confidence can boost your Startups success. Through Science, Jones introduces new businesses and ideas to potential investors and he says that those most likely to make it to the bank are those who<b><i>Commit</i></b>, are<b><i>Genuine</i></b>and who<b><i>Know Themselves</i></b>.\n\nHe explains that often times he sees ideas that are not any better than others nor does the entrepreneur have any greater skill set than the next guy. It comes down to the point of the entrepreneurs confidence in selling both themselves and their vision. His three tips are as follows:\n\n<ol><li>Be Committed  the most successful entrepreneurs are committed to carrying out their vision without letting money or anything else stand in their way.</li><li>Show Yourself Genuine  pitching your idea the way that you think your audience wants to hear it is not the way to go, maintain your personal connection and be authentic!</li><li>Know Who You Are  no man is an island and if you cant navigate the waters you better hire a Captain even if you own the yacht. Be real about your weaknesses and pull others into the fold that can help you in those areas.</li></ol><span>You can read this full</span>article on Young Entrepreneur:<span>(http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/startingup/startup-finance/the-importance-of-being-confident-3-tips-to-startup-success/)</span>\n\n\n\n', 'br', 1369147500, '', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '{filedir_1}shattered_@2X.png', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'http://www.youngentrepreneur.com/startingup/startup-finance/the-importance-of-being-confident-3-tips-to-startup-success/', 'none', '3 Key Confidence Guidelines To Boost Your Startups Success', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(14, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'finance-and-operations', 'none', '', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', 'Alshant L. Squire', 'none', 'As an entrepreneur owning a business is an undertaking that involves preparation, sacrifice and determination.', 'none', 'As an entrepreneur owning a business is an undertaking that involves preparation, sacrifice and determination.\n\n<b>The Objective: Have a</b><b>successful enterprise, and turn an annual profit.</b>\n\nTony Shure and Colin McCabe, Co-Founders of Chopt Creative Salad Company, sat down with Business Accelerator to discuss how they have grown their company from a niche idea into a multi-million dollar business. Even before they opened their first restaurant, Tony and Colin believed they could be betterin their service, in their product, in their operations  creating a standard for their success. In our interview, the duo discusses how keeping their focus helped them overcome a few universal obstacles.\n\n<b>The obstacle: The</b><b>cost</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAfter an offer to manage a friends restaurant left the duo working for only one paycheck, they adjusted their plan and seized the opportunity to work on building their own business model. Colin viewed this setback as an opportunity for the two to grow. we would have taken anything just to learn more about the restaurant business While one was working, the other was working on the business plan or going to the book shop, learning about salads.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul><li>Have you counted up the cost to be an entrepreneur?</li><li>What key things do you need to learn to help you start, grow or maintain your business?</li></ul>&nbsp;\n\n<b>The obstacle: Start</b><b>up funds</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIt was a struggle to raise money with a novel concept. Colin explains of their attempt to find funding for their business. The first of its kind, Chopt has been a leader in salad focused restaurants. The two were adamant about their focus and were confident they did not need to change their business model to succeed. When you are going against the norm, people are not always throwing money at your feet. Being confident in your plan, idea or product is often the main ingredient in the recipe for winning over investors (see 3 Key confidence Guidelines to Boost Your Startup).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul><li>Are you able to present your idea to the Shark Tank?</li><li>What are 3 things that set your business apart from your competitors?</li></ul>&nbsp;\n\n<b>The obstacle:</b><b>Unexpected misfortunes</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nOn their first day of business a computer malfunction left Tony and Colin without a way to collect payment from their customers. This opening day mishap birthed the tradition of free salad day at the opening of every new Chopt location. A tradition which has not only become one of the companys most successful marketing tools but also one if its greatest philanthropic efforts.<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul><li>How can you turn your obstacles into opportunities?</li><li>How does your business give back to the community?</li></ul>\n\n', 'br', 1369147800, '', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', '{filedir_1}shattered_@2X.png', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', 'Business Accelerator Publisher', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Focus On The Objective, Not The Obstacle', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(15, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'leadership-and-growth', 'none', '', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', 'LaToya M. Smith', 'none', 'Great leaders create and build great businesses. Period. Starting a business is only half of the journey to entrepreneurship.', 'none', 'Great leaders create and build\n\ngreat businesses. Period. Starting a business is only half of the journey into\nentrepreneurship. The true test lies in sustaining and growing your firm. No\nmatter what the economic climate is, a leader will keep focused on the\ncompanys vision, finding new opportunities for growth and innovation.\n\n<span>Grant Cardone knows this all too</span>\nwell. The New York Times best-selling author, radio show host, and former star\nand producer for National Geographics show Turnaround King, is a self-made\nmillionaire who founded three multi-million dollar companies that continue to\nthrive under his leadership.\n\n<span>I dont consider myself a great</span>\norganizational leader, says Cardone. I serve my employees and clients better\nworking on the ground level and being involved in all aspects of the business.\nOrganizational leaders sit in ivory towers, attend meetings all day and look\ndown at everyone from their high level view. Thats just not my personality.\n\n<span>Cardone says effective leadership</span>\nmeans getting the job done no matter how busy your schedule is and keeping an\nopen line of communication internally and externally. Here are Cardones five\ntips on how to be a successful leader:\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n<b>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n<b>Walk the Talk:</b><span></span>\n\n<span>If</span>\nyou expect your team to show up on time, value your brand, mission and clients,\nyou need to lead by example explains Cardone. I do what I want others to do or\nto promote. People take note when you show up early and stay late. For example,\nif someone hits me on social media with a problem, I dont comment back.\nInstead, I pick up the phone and call them. I want to talk to them and I want\nmy employees to do that. Communication is a very important part of revenue for\na company and a good leader should return all communication regardless of how\nsmall the company is. Make the time to figure it out.\n\n<b>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n<b>Have a Great Attitude Every Day and Inspire Your</b>\n<b>Team:</b><span></span>\n\n<span>You want to keep</span>\nyour team motivated and you want them to feel invested in the company. Even\nwhen account receivables are not coming in and things are not going according\nto plan, Cardone says, You need to be the light, the beacon and carry a\npositive attitude. If your team feels good about the work theyre doing\neveryday, chances are they wont mind putting in the extra hours and devoting\ntheir best work to the brand. You want to keep your team inspired and\nconstantly let them know that what theyre doing is important and valuable says\nCardone. Every company should have an inspirational story. Acknowledge staff\nthat is doing a great job and dont complain. A good leader will work with the resources\nhe has and inspire and push people to greatness.\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n<b>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n<b>Generate Revenue:</b>\n\n<span>The leader of a</span>\ncompany must ensure the revenue of the organization, says Cardone. Companies\nthat are struggling with revenue are struggling with leadership. Cardone notes\nthat 67% of all companies in America\nbreak even or are losing revenue. No one goes into money to break even, he\nsays. Put your attention on the god of business and that is revenue.\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n<b>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n<b>Execute Ideas:</b><span></span>\n\n<span>Coming up with a</span>\nbrilliant idea and carrying out that idea are two completely different things.\nLeadership gets confused with ideas, he says. You can have a lot of ideas,\nbut if nothing ever gets seen through then theres no point. Leaders arent\nremembered for their aspiration and intentions, theyre remembered for their\nactions and execution.<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n<span>&nbsp;</span>\n\n<b>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n<b>Mind, Body and Soul:</b>\n\n<span>As</span>\na leader you must find a healthy balance between work and your personal\nlife.<span>&nbsp;</span>You must take care of yourself\nand your own mind and be an example of that. My people see me reading, working\nout and taking care of my family. I want them to do the same. The more a companys\nworkforce becomes driven to take care of their health and find balance between\ntheir professional and personal life, the more likely your business will\nsucceed and attract and retain top-\n\n\n\n', 'br', 1369148100, '', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', '{filedir_1}stock-photo-17722659-learn-lead-and-earn.jpg', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', 'Journalist - Black Enterprise Magazine', 'none', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/latoyamsmith', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Leadership Lessons from Grant Cardone', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(16, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'leadership-and-growth', 'none', 'when-it-comes-to-leadership-stock-illustration-24019597-businessman-1200.jpg', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'Harry Colbert, Jr', 'none', 'I didnt realize I had a problem with my leadership style until I didnt have any more troops to lead.', 'none', 'I didnt realize I had a problem with my leadership style until I didnt have any more troops to lead. Thankfully, I got a second chance. But the second time around I had to examine my leadership style and adjust it to best motivate my staff and set my business up for success. I adopted something I like to call the ELF system. ELF is an acronym for ego, listen and flexibility.<h1><i><b><i>Ego </i></b></i><i><b><i>Check yours at the door</i></b></i></h1>\n\n&nbsp; Im the boss! I write the checks. If things fail its my rear on the line. &nbsp; Well, things did fail  and it was my fault! What I didnt realize was just because it was my butt on the line, didnt mean my staff didnt have anything of value to offer. The second time around I took the approach that my staff were coworkers, not underlings. I still maintained the role of boss, but I had to learn the value of each of my coworkers. In fact, many of the suggestions that helped me to grow my business came for staff, who I had empowered with a sense of vested ownership, as we realized when the business did better for me, it did better for us all. &nbsp;<h1><i><b><i>Listen</i></b></i><i><b><i> Dont just hear  listen</i></b></i></h1>\n\n&nbsp; When your staff has a comment, concern or suggestion, dont just hear and move on. Take time to listen to what your staff is saying. Many of my successes have come from staff. If I didnt<i>listen</i>to my staff, I would have lost out. &nbsp;<h1><i><b><i>Flexibility</i></b></i><i><b><i> bend and you wont break</i></b></i></h1><b>&nbsp;</b>In my first foray into business I took an its my way or the highway, approach. Clearly, that didnt work. Learn to adjust to different styles, temperaments and perspectives. Stay committed to your unique vision for your business, but always remain open to change. Remind yourself that your employees are fallible  as are you. Also, remind yourself that your greatest success is on the other side of any turmoil.<span>&nbsp;</span>', 'br', 1369148340, '', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'when-it-comes-to-leadership-stock-illustration-24019597-businessman-360.jpg', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', 'Editor Insight News; Entrepreneur; CEO Thee Urbane Life', 'none', '', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'When It Comes To Leadership, Style Can Equal Substance', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', 'when-it-comes-to-leadership-stock-illustration-24019597-businessman-360.jpg', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none');
