(17, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'marketing', 'none', '5-tips-for-hiring-stock-photo-23826840-social-network-on-blackboard-1200.jpg', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', 'LaToya M. Smith', 'none', 'Most small businesses understand that social media is no longer an optional marketing tool, but they often lack the time...', 'none', 'Most small businesses understand that social media is no longer an optional marketing tool, but they often lack the time, expertise and resources necessary to fully implement, integrate and measure social business as part of their broader business strategy as noted in a July 2012 study by the SMG Group, a technology industry research analysis firm. If that sounds like your company, maybe its time to hire a social media manager. A social media manager is responsible for overseeing your day-to-day content, says Curtis Midkiff, Director of Social Engagement for The Society for Human Resource Management. This includes posting content, monitoring what other people are saying about your company, engaging your audience, building a community and creating conversations about your brand (this will vary based on the guidelines you created). You dont want to cut corners or put your brand in the hands of an amateur, he adds. If youre ready to make the investment, Midkiff provides these tips for small businesses:<b>1. Run from Gurus:</b>In this digital age there are so many self-proclaimed gurus, ninjas, and experts. So how do you know who is really legit? Midkiff advises looking for managers who are practitioners of social mediameaning that they understand the medium but have expertise in other areas. For example, candidates with strong writing, storytelling and editorial skills are useful skill sets in creating engaging content since part of the job is having a conversation with your customers. Midkiff adds, backgrounds in marketing, customer service and/or sales is also beneficial in helping to effectively promote and market your brand. You can benefit from a talent pool of young professionals and graduate students looking for experience.<b><i>Where to find them:</i></b>LinkedIn, Twitter, Mashable, MediaBistro, Craigslist, SocialMediajobs.com, VitaminTalent.com and local colleges and universities communications and marketing departments)<b>2. Collateral Over Klout:</b>Klout measures a persons overall online influence on a scale of 1 to 100. Although Klout has been an important metric among employers as an indicator of someones skill set, Midkiff says this shouldnt be the deciding factor. Instead, give candidates a chance to show you campaigns that theyve worked and their results.<b><i>Questions to ask:</i></b>What platforms are you active on? Can you show me a company of similar size that youve managed and the results of that campaign? What kind of strategies have you worked with in the past? What channels?<b>3. Dont Lock Yourself In:</b>Run from people who try to lock you into yearlong contracts. Start off with a quarterly contract so that you can evaluate their performance from quarter to quarter. You may go through a couple of social media managers to find the right fit. Meet with your manager regularly and track if they are meeting your goals and objectives.<b><i>Questions to ask:</i></b>Do they understand the business goals? Is the content theyre creating relevant? How are they engaging with your customers? Have they increased traffic? Etc.<b>4. Know What Youre Getting:</b>Before you hire a social media manager make sure that you both sit down and create concrete deliverables. It should be very clear on what platforms theyre going to use and how they plan to use those platforms. It doesnt have to get so granular such as a specific number of tweets, content or photos that they will post per day, but you should know what social media channels theyre setting up for you and how they plan to use each platform to meet your goals.<b>5. Dont Turn the Key of Your Brand Over to an Intern:</b>A lot of small businesses are quick to turn their brand over to an intern or a family member who says they know how to use social media to save a few dollars, but remember this person is responsible for coordinating your personal brand. Make the investment because you will get what you put into it. It could be a hit or miss operation. Social media is another avenue for your business to compete and get your product out to the masses. But whomever you hire make sure that you remain hands on as well. You should have administrative access to all of your social media channels.', 'br', 1369148520, '', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', 'generic-img-marketing.jpg', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', 'Journalist - Black Enterprise Magazine', 'none', 'http://www.linkedin.com/in/latoyamsmith', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '5 Tips for Hiring a Social Media Manager ', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '5-tips-for-hiring-stock-photo-23826840-social-network-on-blackboard-360.jpg', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(18, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'marketing', 'none', 'building-a-memorable-brand-stock-photo-900374-color-sampler-1-1200.jpg', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand', 'none', 'Alaina Lewis', 'none', 'Starting a business requires more than just coming up with a great idea, pressing the imaginary Go Button, and then...', 'none', 'Starting a business requires more than just coming up with a great idea, pressing the imaginary Go Button, and then waiting for potential customers to mow you down with a million offers. If it were that easy, everyone would be an entrepreneur. The launch of your business actually means so much more, and in order to transform your great idea into a potential empire, you need to make sure that the ground floor you build it on is<i>branded</i>and solid enough to withstand longevity. Consider these 3 short steps to becoming unforgettable.<b>Step 1: Visual</b>What you see is what you get. This statement can literally make or break your entire business. View your brand from the point of view of the consumer. When selecting your logo, website design, promotional materials, and any other visuals you may need, be certain you have solid and aesthetically pleasing artwork and/or design. Try to keep it simple yet refined. What you present to a client is an unspoken testimony to the type of business theyll assume theyre going to receive if they hire your company. If youre the best event planner in the world, I may miss the opportunity to know that if Im turned off by how youve<i>planned</i>your online presence.<b>Step 2: Social Media</b>Before selecting your name, check the availability of the domain name, Twitter and Facebook names so everything can flow. Your company name and links should match as much as possible.<b>Step 3: Consistency</b>Its important for everything in your brand to match through out all your ventures. You need to ingrain your brand into the minds and memories of everyone watching. If you have a logo, be certain it is on your letterhead, business cards, social media sites, etc. This will be what people will remember and is what will precede you in all your company does. ', 'br', 1369149660, '', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', 'stock-photo-20618931-brand-word-concept.jpg', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', 'Media Impresario; Former Editor of Clutch Magazine', 'none', 'http://www.electricheartmedia.com/', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Building a Memorable and Lasting Brand  Marketing', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', 'building-a-memorable-brand-stock-photo-900374-color-sampler-1-360.jpg', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(19, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'marketing', 'none', 'is-this-thing-on-stock-photo-3477500-mic-in-blue-1200.jpg', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'A Comeaux', 'none', 'So youve written your Mission Statement and your Business Plan is tucked safely on your flash drive.', 'none', 'So youve written your Mission Statement and your Business Plan is tucked safely on your flash drive. After careful editing and final drafts revised for the umpteenth time, youre ready to present your proposal. Then the questions flood and discouragement tickles your pride because youre in the neighborhood of Now What? and you know not who to call to get to your There! Fear not. This may seem like a daunting task, so here are a few tips to move from implementation to execution.<b><i>For starters we need to be clear on who our audience is and how to effectively reach them.</i></b>We live in a cyber-driven world whether we like it or not, but for the sake of marketing its best to make peace with this necessary evil. No matter how time consuming this may seem, the internet and its unlimited reach, is our friend. All social media outlets are free! Reducing costs are key in marketing. Now that we know who were talking to its time to research.<b><i>Watching trends, demands and topics of interest will align our brand with potential customers.</i></b>Youre ready now to join a community to network. Again, social networking is a perfect place to start. At first you may feel like the new kid at the lunch table, but<b>getting involved with like-minded individuals will give you confidence to face the unknown</b>. Here you can ask questions from veterans and novices alike, allowing you to form your own plan of action to succeed. There are online boards to post, share and find information that speaks directly to your business needs. As youve gathered this heap of information, organizing it with realistic deadlines and expectations is critical. Do mock pitches with friends and colleagues to test product and reaction. There will be rejection, dont beat yourself up.<b>Giving your brand a voice to speak for itself is how your it will sell</b>, gain and keep momentum. Supporting others in business is a good way, in turn, to be supported. Stay focused on your original goal and purpose as to why you set out on this journey. Stay positive and persistent.<b><i>Market how you want to be remembered</i></b>. You are the fuel behind your brands voice, be it bold and profitable or timid and flailing, you decide what it will say. Good luck! ', 'br', 1369149780, '', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'stock-photo-4622129-holding-a-megaphone.jpg', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', 'Entrepreneur; Author; Columnist - Six Brown Chicks ', 'none', 'http://www.sixbrownchicks.com', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Is This Thing On? How to Give Your Brand a Voice', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', 'is-this-thing-on-stock-photo-3477500-mic-in-blue-360.jpg', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(20, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'sales', 'none', 'how-to-not-crossstock-photo-10567012-tango-1200.jpg', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'A Comeaux', 'none', 'When you think of a salesman its oftentimes perceived as someone trying to sell something we dont need. ', 'none', 'When you think of a salesman its oftentimes perceived as someone trying to sell something we dont need. The perfunctory pitch rehearsed and well versed to seal the deal can be a plague more so than produce profit. No matter if you own the company, or youre a consumer in search for a bargain, we<b>ALL</b>play an integral part in the buy/sell cycle. Theres a delicate dance of getting what you want at the price you find unbeatable. In turn, selling said product at an attractive price as to not upset your expenses seems to be the formula we all want to know the secret to. How can all mediums be met?<b><i>A great salesman knows how to deliver to the customer at their appeasement without crossing the sacred laws of the bottom line.</i></b>The best scenario for all parties involved would be to find out exactly what your customer is looking for, who else is selling it and at what price can you sell it without your shareholders getting clipped.<b><i>As a business owner, you want to provide your customers with a deal.</i></b>Knowing we all love to see sale signs, we must also understand the need to profit in order to stay afloat. As a consumer we know what we want and usually are not afraid to shop around until we find that product/bargain balance that this economy demands. Buy smart. Sell with integrity. Be it books or a service, we all provide a need/want and we all have bottom lines to respect.<i>The best way to not cross this line is to think like youre a consumer</i>, even when you own the company. In essence, owners are still consumers! We have to be as sensitive with our buyers as we expect sellers to be to us when roles are reversed. Everyone on every level has a bottom line. The beauty of sales lies in the beast of this tango. We can all take turns on the sales floor. ', 'br', 1369149960, '', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'stock-photo-15889548-calculator-and-pen.jpg', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', 'Entrepreneur; Author; Columnist ', 'none', 'http://www.sixbrownchicks.com/', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'How Not to Cross the Bottom Line', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', 'how-to-not-crossstock-photo-10567012-tango-360.jpg', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none'),
(21, 1, 5, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, 'sales', 'none', 'turn-existing-customers-stock-photo-17920441-waiting-in-line-1200.jpg', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'Alaina Lewis', 'none', 'Ever wonder how computer companies are able to get customers to rush to their local store and purchase the newest version...', 'br', 'Ever wonder how computer companies are able to get customers to rush to their local store and purchase the newest version of their product? Or why do we as consumers feel we need 5 different devices by our favorite brand just to send an email? A computer, laptop, tablet, and cell phone essentially do the same thing, yet we never hesitate to run out there, and quadruple up on our technology. This practice is known as turning existing customers into returning customers. This is one of the keys to garnering repeat success in your entrepreneurial venture. Here are some simple tips to turn your existing customers into returning customers.<b>Step 1: The Reinvention of a Design:</b>Welcome to the world of 2.0, 3.0, and beyond. As evolution occurs in the world of technology, ones business must also evolve in order to stay afloat and continually competitive. If youre a personal business which focuses on web design, maybe in the past youve started your client out with a basic website. As you observe their company growth, consider going back to them with a proposal for a more dynamic website which would be a better reflection of where their business is today. This is a very good way to create a mutual justice to your client/contractor relationship.<b>Step 2: Being a Multi-Hyphenated Business:</b>Offering more than one type of service gives you an opportunity to sell your current clientele something else they might need. If youve produced a television commercial for them, maybe now you can assist them with the marketing/pr they may need to get this commercial out to the public. You dont just sell a customer a haircut; you become an expert in coloring, styling, and beyond. The key is to keep the business in your backyard, versus giving them an opportunity to find another company who may already do it all. Then what would they need you for?<b>Step 3: Updating Your Clients On What You</b><b>Have Going On:</b>Sending out monthly newsletters to your clients/subscription list is a great way to allow people the opportunity to see what youre working on and through unspoken suggestion; its a good way to sell them something they may not have known they needed in the first place. If I didnt know that your company also offered video production, but I see that youve created a dynamic visual for someone else, I may approach you about the same service for my business. ', 'br', 1369150020, '', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'stock-photo-352174-come-again.jpg', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', 'Media Impresario; Former Editor of Clutch Magazine ', 'none', 'http://www.electricheartmedia.com/', 'none', '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'Turn Existing Customers Into Returning Customers ', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 'http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1370439127/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7069002/entry_id/0_bkt05hhd', 'none', 'http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1370439284/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7069002/entry_id/0_fikktujq', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'xhtml', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', '', 'none', 0, 'none', '', 'none',